# GREAT Enrichment Pipeline (Post-motif analysis)

## Step 1: Prepare BED files for upload
# Ensure BED files have 3 columns only: chr, start, end
cut -f1-3 input.bed > input_clean.bed

## Step 2: Upload to [GREAT](http://great.stanford.edu/public/html/)
# Options to set:
# - Species Assembly: Choose hg38 for human or mm10 for mouse
# - Test Regions: Upload your `input_clean.bed`
# - Background Regions: You can skip this or upload a matched background if required

## Step 3: Download results
# - Enrichment tables (GO, Mouse/Human Phenotype, etc.)
# - Region-gene association graphs
# - Save PDF/CSV summaries for report use
